application_type_full: Prior Approval: Change of use - offices to dwellinghouses
description: Change of use of building from offices (Use class B1a) to residential (Use class C3) to accommodate 331 residential units (Class O, 56 day Prior Approval Process)
decision_conditions: The proposal falls within the provisions of Schedule 2, Part 3, Class O of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 No. 596 (as amended by the General Permitted Development Order 332 of 2016). Prior Approval is required and given . | The development hereby approved shall be retained in accordance with reports and drawing title number(s):

Noise impact assessment prepared by Bickerdlike Allen Partners reference A11075-R02-V02-LBA dated 08/05/2017; Phase 1 contamination assessment report prepared by GB Card & Partners reference GB/422 Rev. 2 dated May 2017; Transport assessment report prepared Paul Mew Associates ref P1678 West Gate House TA v2 080517; Flood risk statement prepared by Ardent consulting engineers Ref. 171130-01 dated Apriil 2017; GA-P-SL dated 08/05/2017; GA-PD-SP-LG dated 08/05/2017; GA-PD-SP-LG dated 08/05/2017; EX_SP dated 28/04/2017; GA-PD-P-LG dated 08/05/2017; GA-PD-P-UG dated 08/05/2017; GA-PD-P-L01 dated 08/05/2017; GA-PD-P-L02-L04 dated 24/07/2017; GA-PD-P-L05 dated 24/07/2017;GA-PD-P-L06 dated 08/05/2017; EX_P_L01 dated 08/05/2017; EX_P_L02-05 dated 28/04/2017; EX_P_L06 dated 28/04/2017; EX_P_LG dated 28/04/2017; EX_P_UG dated 28/04/2017; GA-EX-EX-N-S dated 08/05/2017; GA-EL-EX-W-E dated 08/05/2017; GA_EL_N_S dated 08/05/2017; GA_S_AA_BB dated 08/05/2017; GA-S-EX-AA-BB dated 08/05/2017; GA-S-EX-CC-DD dated 08/05/2017; GA-S-EX-EE dated 08/05/2017; GA-S-EX-EE dated 08/05/2017.

REASON: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning. | Sixty six (66) car parking spaces shall be provided onsite in accordance with all adopted standards prior to occupation of the building and be continuously available and retained for the life of the development hereby approved. Of these spaces:
o	Thirty three (33) are to be accessible car parking spaces and blue badge spaces; and
o	Thirteen (13) of the car parking spaces will have active electric vehicle charging facilities.

REASON: To ensure adequate provision of car parking and promote sustainable patterns of transport in accordance with Policies 1.1 f & 2.8 g of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), Policies 6.1, 6.9, 6.10, 6.11, 6.12 and 6.13 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012). | Cycle storage for a minimum of three hundred and fifty eight (358) bicycles shall be provided onsite in accordance with all adopted standards prior to occupation of the building and be continuously available and retained for the life of the development hereby approved.

REASON: To provide adequate bicycle storage to align with Sustainable Transport SPG and Policy 6.9 and 6.13 of the London Plan (2016). | Details demonstrating free car club membership is to be provided for all residents for a period of 3 years is be submitted and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to occupation of the site.

REASON: To promote sustainable patterns of transport in accordance with policies 1.1 f & 2.8 g of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), Policies 6.1, 6.9, 6.10, 6.11, & 6.12 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012). | An updated travel plan with clear target sets is to be submitted 8 months after initial occupation to the local planning authority for approval. The travel plan shall include the survey results, to be conducted 6 months after initial occupation, to establish the baseline trip generation modal split for which the travel plan targets are set and shall satisfy Transport for London ATTrBuTe test.

REASON: To promote sustainable patterns of transport and in the interests of highway and pedestrian safety accordance with policies 1.1 f & 2.8 g of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), Policies 6.1, 6.9, 6.10, 6.11, & 6.12 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012). | Prior to commencement of works, details shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority demonstrating the conversion complies with the recommendations of the noise impact assessment prepared by Bickerdlike Allen Partners reference A11075-R02-V02-LBA dated 08/05/2017.

REASON: To protect the amenity of occupants and neighbouring properties, in accordance with policy 7A of Ealing Council's Development Management Policies DPD (adopted 2013) and Policy 7.15 of the London Plan (2016). | The final Construction Logistics Plan (CLP) containing measures to minimise the impact of the construction of the development on the local road network, including the TLRN (Hanger Lane Gyratory) shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of works.

REASON: In the interest of the amenity of adjoining occupiers and to minimise highway and traffic impact during the course of the works, in accordance with policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan (2013), Policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012 and Policy 5.18 of the London Plan (2016). | A Delivery & Servicing Plan (DSP) shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the occupation of the site.

REASON: In the interest of the amenity of adjoining occupiers and to minimise highway and traffic impact during the course of the works, in accordance with policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan (2013), Policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012 and Policy 5.18 of the London Plan (2016). | All vehicles associated with the development must only park/stop at permitted locations and within the time periods permitted by existing restrictions.

REASON: In the interest of the amenity of adjoining occupiers and to minimise highway and traffic impact in accordance with policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan (2013), Policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012 and Policy 5.18 of the London Plan (2016).
